    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. log transformation makes sense for the price scale. what about the outliers specifically though? if i use robust regression, are there specific types you'd recommend for this kind of skewed distribution? also do you think i should check for heteroscedasticity too?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For your skewed distribution, M-estimation or Huber regression within a robust framework are good starting points, as they balance efficiency with resistance to outliers. You absolutely should check for heteroscedasticity, as non-constant variance in residuals can make your standard errors unreliable, even if the distribution looks okay otherwise. If you find heteroscedasticity, using weighted least squares (WLS) can correct the standard errors, which is a very interpretable fix.",
      "source": "target",
